.TH JD 1 2024-09-09 "jd @tag@"
.
.SH NAME
.
jd \- navigation and manipulation tool for johnny.decimal systems
.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.
.SY jd
.RB { " \-h " | " \-\-help " }
.SY jd
.RB { " \-v " | " \-\-version " }
.YS
.
.SY jd
.BR "\<command\> " ...
.YS
.
.SH DESCRIPTION
.
.P
The
.B jd
utility is a simple but powerful tool to navigate and manipulate johnny.decimal
systems with. Its functionality is compartmentalized into various subcommands,
which are listed under \fIJD commands\fP in the \fIOPTIONS\fP section.
.P
Note: Before using
.B jd\c
, you should probably configure the \fIjd_root\fP option. For more
information on how to do this, please refer to
.BR jd-config (1)
and
.BR jd.conf (5).
.
.SH OPTIONS
.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Display a short help message.
.
.TP
.B \-v, \-\-version
Display version information.
.
.SS JD commands
.
.TP
.BR jd-config (1)
Get and set configuration options of the \fBjd\fP utility.
.
.TP
.BR jd-ls (1)
List directories of the johnny.decimal system.
.
.TP
.BR jd-path (1)
Display the path to a directory of the johnny.decimal system.
.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.
.TP
.B 0
SUCCESS: Everything went as it should.
.
.TP
.B 1
ERROR: An error outside of below categories occurred.
.
.TP
.B 2
NOT_FOUND: The target of a search operation was not found.
.
.TP
.B 3
INPUT_ERROR: Invalid input was provided by the user.
.
.TP
.B 4
CONFIG_ERROR: An error occurred in the configuration mechanism.
.
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.
.TP
.I JD_ROOT
This environment variable can be used to override the configured file system
path to the johnny.decimal system's root directory. Simply set it to the
desired path.
.TP
.I XDG_CONFIG_HOME
Path to the user-specific configuration directory. Defaults to
\fI\(ti/.config\fP. See \fIFILES\fP.
.
.SH FILES
.
.TP
.I $XDG_CONFIG_HOME/jd/jd.conf
This is the main \fBjd\fP configuration file. See
.BR jd.conf (5).
.
.SH EXAMPLES
.
.P
Show the help message:
.IP
.EX
jd --help
.EE
.
.P
Display version information:
.IP
.EX
jd --version
.EE
.
.P
For more information and examples about jd commands, please refer to the
respective command's manual.
.
.SH SEE ALSO
.
.nh
.BR jd-config (1),
.BR jd-ls (1),
.BR jd-path (1),
.BR jd.conf (5)
.
.P
.UR https://johnnydecimal.com
.UE
